Influx_4331_proof
=================

Container containing a docker compose environment to reproduce https://github.com/influxdb/influxdb/issues/4331

This demo spins up a 5 node InfluxDB cluster containing a test database with replication=2 as well as a test data generator which feeds it simple data points.

Requirements
------------

- Docker
- Docker Compose
- docker0 set to default IP of 172.17.42.1

Reproducing
===========

Start the containers
```
./start.sh
```

In another window, open the cli.  A containerized wrapper is provided with all the args.  Show the shards.

```
./influx_cli.sh 
Connected to http://172.17.42.1:8186 version 0.9.5-nightly-b079d20
InfluxDB shell 0.9.5-nightly-b079d20
> show shards
name: _internal
---------------
id      start_time              end_time                expiry_time             owners
3       2015-10-06T00:00:00Z    2015-10-07T00:00:00Z    2015-10-14T00:00:00Z    5
4       2015-10-06T00:00:00Z    2015-10-07T00:00:00Z    2015-10-14T00:00:00Z    1
5       2015-10-06T00:00:00Z    2015-10-07T00:00:00Z    2015-10-14T00:00:00Z    2
6       2015-10-06T00:00:00Z    2015-10-07T00:00:00Z    2015-10-14T00:00:00Z    3
7       2015-10-06T00:00:00Z    2015-10-07T00:00:00Z    2015-10-14T00:00:00Z    4


name: testdb
------------
id      start_time              end_time                expiry_time             owners
1       2015-10-06T00:00:00Z    2015-10-07T00:00:00Z    2015-10-14T00:00:00Z    4,1
2       2015-10-06T00:00:00Z    2015-10-07T00:00:00Z    2015-10-14T00:00:00Z    2,3
```

Disconnect from the cli and reconnect to the node without any testdb shards (5 in this example).
The wrapper accepts the node number to connect to as the first argument.
Run the select with the error.

```
./influx_cli.sh 5
Connected to http://172.17.42.1:8586 version 0.9.5-nightly-b079d20
InfluxDB shell 0.9.5-nightly-b079d20
> SELECT mean("value") FROM "testdata" WHERE time > now() - 15m GROUP BY time(1s)
ERR: invalid character 'j' looking for beginning of value
> 
```

Also, gaps in the data can be seen by connecting to one of the nodes with some of the shards and running the above query.
